parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or die, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's voltage gauge reading is low
the vehicle feels like it's going to die out
the vehicle has problems getting out of gear
the brakes are bad
the muffler has a big hole in it
and coolant leaks from the intake manifold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the intake manifold can cause coolant leaks, leading to engine damage and overheating.
symptoms: Coolant leaks from the intake manifold
the vehicle has problems getting out of gear
and the brakes are bad.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
and the ABS light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake caliper can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The rear brake caliper freezes up
causing a grinding sign
and the rotor is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the vehicle vibrates when the brakes are applied
the vehicle makes a loud noise when the brakes are applied
and the vehicle is unable to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat mount can cause the seat to break loose, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat breaks loose and tips rearward
and the seat mount has a rippled appearance of metal fatigue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper switch can cause the wipers to malfunction or become inoperative, reducing visibility during inclement weather and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers work intermittently
the wipers do not turn on
there is a delay in wiper operation
the wipers only work when the turn signal is on
the wiper switch is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper system can cause the wipers to malfunction or become inoperative, reducing visibility during inclement weather and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not work
the wipers work intermittently
the wiper system fails to operate in hot weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor ventilation in the vehicle can cause mold growth, leading to unpleasant odors and potentially harmful health effects.
symptoms: Strong mold odor
poor ventilation within the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exterior rearview mirror can cause debris to break loose and potentially cause injury or damage.
symptoms: The exterior rearview mirror exploded
pieces of mirror flew into the window and cut the driver's lip.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Moisture Build-up on Windshield and Windows
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Moisture build-up on the windshield and windows can reduce visibility, making it difficult to drive safely.
symptoms: Moisture builds up on the windshield and all windows in cold weather
windshield fogs up when the vehicle is left parked outside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent sounding of the horn without driver input can cause accidents, near-misses, and distractions, posing a significant safety risk to the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: The horn sounds without being touched
sounds while driving
sounds while parked
and may cause sudden reactions or evasive maneuvers from other drivers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off without warning, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings, especially on highways or at night.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off without warning
all electrical components become inoperable
and the engine light may come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings, especially on highways or at night.
symptoms: The alternator overheats
fails
or needs repeated repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings, especially on highways or at night.
symptoms: The ignition lock cylinder is broken
preventing the key from turning
or the ignition switch malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tampering with the airbag system can cause the airbag to malfunction or not deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag on/off switch was installed
and the wire connecting the fuel injection system to the computer was cut.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to shift, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle is hard to shift out of neutral unless the parking brake is engaged and then disengaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, especially during inclement weather, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers only operate when the left turn signal is on due to a broken wire in the wiper switch.
